   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The conveyor belt is tensioned and guided via the tensioning station. The tensioning pulley
         (1) is moved in a straight line via tensioning spindles (2), thereby increasing or reducing
         the tension of the conveyor belt. The tensioning pulley is mounted on two pedestal bearings
         (4) by means of a shaft (3) and is able to rotate. A rotary survey is mounted at the end of
         the shaft.</p>
